+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Jwyqbf5MwdoU9tEFWLeVWG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019VNrkQMS22AwLferwCNa5s","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-collab-editor-design.md","content":"# Collaborative Real-Time Document Editor - Design\n\n## Architecture\n\nLayered architecture with clear separation:\n\n```\nsrc/\n  types.ts       - Shared TypeScript types/interfaces\n  database.ts    - SQLite database layer (better-sqlite3)\n  ot.ts          - Operational Transform engine\n  routes.ts      - Express REST API routes\n  websocket.ts   - WebSocket connection handler\n  server.ts      - createApp factory, wires everything together\n```\n\n## Data Model\n\nUses the provided `schema.sql` with three tables:\n- `documents` - id (UUID), title, content, timestamps\n- `versions` - document_id, version (integer), content snapshot, operation JSON\n- `active_connections` - tracking connected WebSocket clients\n\n## REST API\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| POST | /docs | Create document (title, optional content) |\n| GET | /docs | List all documents |\n| GET | /docs/:id | Get single document |\n| PUT | /docs/:id | Update document (title, content) |\n| DELETE | /docs/:id | Delete document |\n| GET | /docs/:id/versions | Get version history |\n\nAll responses are JSON. Errors return appropriate HTTP status codes.\n\n## WebSocket Protocol\n\n**Connection:** `ws://host:port/docs/:id/ws`\n\n**Message Types (JSON):**\n\n```typescript\n// Server → Client: Initial sync on connect\n{ type: \"sync\", content: string, version: number }\n\n// Client → Server: Edit operation\n{ type: \"operation\", operation: Operation, version: number }\n\n// Server → Client: Broadcast other client's edit\n{ type: \"broadcast\", operation: Operation, version: number, clientId: string }\n\n// Server → Client: Acknowledge client's own operation\n{ type: \"ack\", version: number }\n\n// Server → Client: Error\n{ type: \"error\", message: string }\n```\n\n## Operational Transform\n\n**Operations:**\n- `insert(position, text)` - Insert text at position\n- `delete(position, count)` - Delete count characters at position\n\n**Transform Rules (transform(op1, op2) where op1 arrived first):**\n\n1. **insert vs insert:** If op2.pos <= op1.pos, shift op1.pos right by op2.text.length. Otherwise no change.\n2. **insert vs delete:** If op2.pos < op1.pos, shift op1.pos left by min(op2.count, op1.pos - op2.pos). If op2.pos >= op1.pos, no change.\n3. **delete vs insert:** If op2.pos <= op1.pos, shift op1.pos right by op2.text.length. If op2.pos > op1.pos but within delete range, adjust count.\n4. **delete vs delete:** Handle overlapping ranges by adjusting position and count.\n\n**Server flow:**\n1. Client sends operation based on version V\n2. Server retrieves all operations from V to current version\n3. Server transforms client operation against each intervening operation\n4. Server applies transformed operation to document content\n5. Server increments version, stores in versions table\n6. Server broadcasts transformed operation to other clients\n7. Server sends ack with new version to originating client\n\n## Persistence\n\n- SQLite via better-sqlite3 (synchronous API)\n- Document content updated in-place on each operation\n- Each operation stored in versions table with version number\n- Version 0 = initial document creation\n- active_connections table cleaned on server shutdown\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- Invalid JSON → error message back to client\n- Unknown document → 404 / WebSocket close\n- Invalid operation (out of bounds) → error message, operation rejected\n- Malformed operation → error message, operation rejected\n\n## Concurrency\n\n- Server-authoritative: single source of truth\n- All operations serialized through the server\n- SQLite transactions ensure atomicity\n- Per-document room tracking for WebSocket broadcasts\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":107,"cache_read_input_tokens":25887,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":107},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d2897688-e6bb-4a62-94c8-e0f26f54d2bf","uuid":"a4948999-667f-4306-b016-3e03b70b299f"}
